Transport Minister Fikile Mbalula delivered his department's budget vote. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Transport Minister Fikile Mbalula says the formalisation of the taxi industry is in progress. Talks to reform the industry kicked off last year when Mbalula launched the National Taxi Lekgotla Public Discourse Platform. WATCH: 'Gauteng taxi bosses law unto themselves' The minister has been delivering his department's budget vote. Meanwhile, Mbalula says his department is considering having longer operating hours while using technology at driving licence centres.